The 50 Gi offers a 185 grain solid copper hollowpoint at 1,200 FPS, a 230 Grain Solid Copper Hollowpoint at 1,000 FPS, a 275 Jacketed Hollwopoint at 875 FPS or a 300 Grain Jacketed FLat Point at 700 FPS. It is more powerfull than a 45 acp but these low pressure loads recoil the same or less than 45 loads

title: For Sale:  Norinco SKS "M",  Paratrooper, Built to use AK mags!
location: In order of preference: South, East, North, Indianapolis, Indiana
postcontent:
My research into this particular SKS leads me to believe that this rifle was made after the Clinton assault rifle ban and made by Norinco for export to the civilian market.  It has no bayonet or bayonet lug and has a "hunting" look to the stock (so as not to scare those who fear "assault weapons").  

For those of you who like a shorter, more maneuverable SKS, this paratrooper fits the bill.  Compared to it's longer SKS cousins, this 16" barrel SKS is much more manageable.  I think this would serve you well if you were to use this weapon for home defense; the longer SKSs would be too cumbersome for "inside" fighting.  This SKS (like most) has a milled receiver for incredible durability.  Because it was built by Norinco to use AK mags (and is not a conversion) I call it "The Poor Man's AK".  Some people have told me that SKSs tend to be more accurate that AKs, I'm not sure but I can tell you that this rifle is quite accurate.  

This SKS also comes with it's original sling and a Tasco scope which is about the same age as the rifle.  The scope mount on the rifle was engineered in such a way that you could look under it and utilize the iron sights if you so desired (see pic below).  

Like most AKs and SKSs this rifle has the adjustable front sight that allows you to (theoretically) use your iron sights for targets out to 1,000 meters.  Practically speaking, my sights are spot on for up to 30 yards or so, after that distance I need the scope anyway ;-) .  The front sight is nicely protected in a round shroud.  For those of you who have an AK front sight adjustment tool, it will work on this SKS.  

The blonde wood stock is what came with the gun and shows some light wear but not too bad.  No visible rust on the gun and the barrel's inside is very clean.  I don't know if all the numbers match because when I have taken it apart to clean it I forget to check.  If it is make or break for a serious buyer I'll look into it.  I can tell you it functions flawlessly and I've kept it clean and lightly lubricated.  

Because of the run on guns that is going on I've decided to put this one up for sale and see how it goes.  If it doesn't sell that's ok too.

I'm not interested in most trades.  The only thing I might trade for would be an AK (with some $$ coming from me, for the right gun), but partial payment can be made in ammo as well (7.62 x 39, 9 mm, 40 S&W, 22 Long Rifle).  If you are offering your gun in trade you must send me a few pictures with your offer.

Note: The plastic mag in the 3rd picture is for demonstration purposes only.  No magazines are being offered with this gun.

I prefer face to face near Indianapolis, any part of town except downtown or the west side (I'm hardly ever over on the west side anymore).   I need to see an Indiana DL and LTCH.  No paperwork, I just need to know you're not a felon or from out of state.
